push first DECREMENTS ESP by 4, then places its OPERAND into the contents of the 32-bit location at address [ESP]

push eax — push eax on the stack
push [var] — push the 4 bytes at address var onto the stack

push algorithm:
ESP = ESP - 4
mov [ESP], <push operand>

==============================

pop first moves the 4 bytes located at memory location [SP] into the specified register or memory location, and then increments SP by 4.

pop edi — pop the top element of the stack into EDI.
pop [ebx] — pop the top element of the stack into memory at the four bytes starting at location EBX.

pop algorithm:
mov [ESP], <pop operand>
ESP = ESP + 4

